	  This time the accept call keeps working right for non-blocking
	  sockets.

2006-01-05 14:00  loose

	* configure.in: BugID: 557

	  The check for Boost.Threads causes havoc for other packages,
	  because the .so file is in a non-standard directory and
	  automake/libtool does not add a -rpath for this .so file (I've
	  posted a question about this on the automake mailing list).

2006-01-05 09:58  overeem

	* include/Common/LofarLog4Cplus.h, test/testLogger.cc: BugID: 146
	  Created patch for log4cplus 1.0.2 and include global-init.h in
	  the header- file of the lofarlogger. Updated the testprogram to
	  test the static initialize class also.

