2005-08-03 12:57  romein

	* src/BlobHeader.h: BugID: 51 Remove explicit BlobHeader::
	  qualification where it is not allowed; the xlc compiler is picky
	  about it.

2005-07-18 09:35  loose

	* src/: ComplexBuiltinFP.h, ComplexC99.h: %[ER: 70]% clog cannot be
	  used with PVSS

2005-07-08 09:42  diepen

	* src/: ComplexBuiltinFP.h, ComplexC99.h: %[ER: 70]% clog cannot be
	  used with PVSS

2005-07-06 15:44  romein

	* src/: Timer.cc, Timer.h: %[ER: ]% - Added print-on-destruction
	  option to constructor.  This simplifies profiling   how much time
	  is spent in a region of code:

	    void myFunction()
	    {
		static NSTimer timer("myFunction", true);
		timer.start();
		doWork();
		timer.stop();
	    }

	    and the timer's results will be printed at program exit.

	  - Added support for PathScale compiler

2005-07-06 14:32  loose

	* AUTHORS, COPYING, INSTALL, NEWS, README, configure.in: %[ER: 0]%

	  Merged relevant changes from the release 2.2 branch into the main
	  development line.

2005-07-06 10:15  overeem

	* src/: StringUtil.cc, StringUtil.h: %[ER:285]% Upgrade ACC 1.0 to
	  1.1 ParameterSet is now in ACC/APS.  ProceControl is now in
	  ACC/PLC.  ParameterSet getInt changed to getInt32.

2005-07-01 18:16  loose

	* test/tComplex.cc: %[ER: 247]%

	  * Removed check for which header file to include, because this is
	  now checked	by lofar_complex.h. Also uses make{d,f}complex
	  macro now.  * Fixed memory leak.

2005-07-01 16:25  loose

	* src/ComplexBuiltinFP.h: %[ER: 247]%

	  After `clog' had been added to the type definitions in
	  lofar_iostream.h, a collision occurred between the clog()
	  function and the clog global object. clog() and all other global
	  functions now have an explicit global namespace indication.

2005-07-01 16:16  loose

	* src/LofarLogCout.cc: %[ER: 0]%

	  It is better to use the buffered output stream clog, instead of
	  the unbuffered stream cerr, because no locking is being done
	  within the LofarLogCout routines when logging messages. Hence,
	  the use of clog avoids two or more messages getting completely
	  mixed up.

2005-07-01 16:13  loose

	* src/LofarLogCout.h: %[ER: 0]%

	  The macro AUTO_FUNCTION_NAME should be used instead of
	  __PRETTY_FUNCTION__, because the former is guaranteed to be
	  defined, whereas the latter is not.

2005-07-01 15:49  loose

	* src/lofar_iostream.h: %[ER: 161]%

	  Added missing clog declaration.

2005-06-10 13:08  overeem

	* src/lofar_datetime.h: %[ER:279]% Bring Boost date time into Lofar
	  namespace.

2005-06-10 12:18  loose

	* configure.in: %[ER: 252]%

	  Moved LimitExec.cc to LCS/Tools, so that it does not depend on,
	  e.g., liblog4cplus.so. However, now LCS/Common depends on
	  LCS/Tools.

