2004-11-22 11:28  loose

	* test/tRunOnNode.out: %[PR: 119]%

	  Removed. It only contained information from the logger, which
	  should always be discarded, because it might differ between build
	  variants and even run-time environments.

2004-11-22 09:54  loose

	* src/LofarLogCout.h: %[ER: 161]%

	  Stupid mistake: forgot to include lofar_sstream.h. The code
	  compiled fine with threads enabled, because in that case,
	  Thread.h would be included, which would, in turn, include
	  lofar_sstream.h. This obviously failed miserably when configured
	  without thread support.

2004-11-22 09:51  loose

	* src/backward/Debug.cc: %[ER: 161]%

	  Added warning comment.

2004-11-19 15:44  loose

	* src/LimitExec.cc: %[PR: 118]%

	  Fixed. LimitExec now returns -1 when the child was terminated by
	  a signal; else it returns the child's exit status.

2004-11-19 15:08  loose

	* src/LofarLogCout.h: %[ER: 161]%

	  * Fixed name clash with preprocessor macro Debug.  * Added
	  explicit LOFAR::Debug specification in some macros.  * Reversed
	  trace level numbering in output message, in order to comply with
	   the trace level numbering of log4cplus.  * Fixed formatting bug
	  in Debug::stream_time().  * Reordered code because ssprintf() was
	  used before being declared.

2004-11-19 14:59  loose

	* src/backward/Debug.cc: %[ER: 161]%

	  * Removed explicit std:: namespace specifications.  * Removed
	  spurious ends in an ostringstream.  * Tracer::startMsg() and
	  Tracer::endMsg() now use "TRACE" instead of "trace",	 in order
	  to be compliant with the LofarLogger format.

2004-11-19 14:53  loose

	* src/Debug.h: %[ER: 161]%

	  * Added deprecated warning.  * Fixed formatting bug in
	  Debug::stream_time() * Reordered code, because ssprintf() was
	  used before being declared.

