2004-03-15 10:35  wierenga

	* src/Makefile.am: %[ER:70]%

	  Cannot use if HAVE_LOG4CPLUS because its definition from
	  autoconf_share/lofar_external.m4 is not recognised by older
	  versions of autoconf/automake.

2004-03-12 13:02  wierenga

	* src/LofarLogger.h: %[ER:70 ]% Add #undef THROW before #define
	  THROW to undefine the definition from Exception.h.

2004-03-12 09:45  wierenga

	* src/LimitExec.cc: %[ER: 70]%

	  Renamed LimitExec.c to LimitExec.cc to make sure it is compiled
	  with the c++ compiler.

2004-03-12 09:44  wierenga

	* src/Makefile.am: %[ER:70 ]%

	  Removed use of += within LOG4CPLUS condition. It doesn't work on
	  older automake versions.  Renamed LimitExec.c to LimitExec.cc
	  because the gcc compiler could not link with the c++ log4cplus
	  library! This is a problem caused by the fact that for any
	  configured packages all libraries are unconditionally added to
	  LDADD. What we should really have is a LOG4CPLUS_LDADD which can
	  then be used as needed.

2004-03-11 14:21  wierenga

	* configure.in, src/Makefile.am: %[ER:70]%

	  Compile in LofarLogger only when log4cplus is correctly
	  configured.

