2003-12-12 15:25  brentjens

	* src/LofarTypes.h: %[PR: 53]%

	  Added #if(HAVE_QT) directive to prevent nameclash with QT
	  definitions of uchar. If QT is present, load qglobal.h, else
	  maintain original "using" declarations.

	  In order to prevent future namclashes, the using declarations
	  should be moved to the .cc files that need them. Ideally, there
	  should not be any "using" declarations in any .h file.

