2003-09-30 13:31  smirnov

	* src/Debug.cc, src/Debug.h, test/tDebug.out: %[ER: 16]% Tied the
	  debug stream to cerr rather than cout. This necessitated a change
	  to the dprintf() macro.  Throw() now dumps the exception message
	  to the debug stream at level 1.

2003-09-30 12:38  loose

	* src/Debug.h: %[ER: 19]% Forgot to modify one instance of
	  HAVE___FUNCTION__. Did it now.

2003-09-29 18:00  loose

	* src/: Exception.cc, Exception.h: %[ER: 19]% Now this is rather
	  awkward... The THROW macro does not work with stringstream.  It
	  never did, and never could. I was so eager to minimize
	  compile-time dependencies that I did not want to include
	  <sstream>. But my approach failed miserably, because you cannot
	  construct a stringstream using a number of arguments glued
	  together using operator<<. You really must shift these arguments
	  into the stringstream within the THROW macro. Hence, I got rid of
	  the extra constructor taking an ostringstream as its first
	  argument, for I don't see any use for it anymore. Sigh! I really
	  need to do better unit testing.

2003-09-29 17:44  smirnov

	* src/Debug.h, test/tDebug.cc: %[ER: 16]% Based Debug (and Assert)
	  errors off of LCS::Exception.  Cleaned up Assert macros.

2003-09-19 15:40  loose

	* configure.in: %[ER: 30]% Added check for PRETTY_FUNCTION.

2003-09-19 15:39  loose

	* src/HEADER.h: %[ER: 30]% Changed definition of include guard.
	  Doxygen only ignores #ifndef and not #if !defined(), and we do
	  not want our include guards documented, do we?

2003-09-19 15:31  loose

	* src/Exception.h: %[ER: 19]% Added documentation.

2003-09-19 15:23  loose

	* src/Debug.h: %[ER: 19]% Changed check for HAVE___FUNCTION__ into
	  check for both HAVE_PRETTY_FUNCTION and HAVE_FUNCTION which are
	  defined by configure.

2003-09-15 12:39  smirnov

	* src/: Makefile.am, debug_methods.g: %[ER: 16]% Moved
	  debug_methods.g to CEP/CPA/GlishUtil

2003-08-27 15:13  diepen

	* src/Lorrays.h: Removed erronous CVS diff lines

2003-08-22 12:15  loose

	* src/Exception.h: Moved macro definitions outside of namespace
	  LCS. It doesn't matter to the compiler, cause preprocessor macros
	  are global by definition, but it might confuse the human reader.
	  Removed the macro EXCEPTION, because it cannot be used outside
	  namespace LCS.

2003-08-21 18:25  loose

	* src/Makefile.am: Added Exception.{h,cc}

2003-08-21 18:24  loose

	* src/: Exception.cc, Exception.h: Initial version

2003-08-21 18:21  loose

	* src/: HEADER.cc, HEADER.h: Changed comment '//' into '//#'.
	  Doxygen will be told to ignore the latter type of comment.

2003-08-21 13:20  diepen

